libcaptury
------------------------------------------
Captury is a realtime multimedia capturing framework for currently OpenGL
video (to be extended to XShm and audio/alsa soon). Its uses are e.g. for
capturing video from external OpenGL applications (via captury itself) and is
currently also used by KDE's kwin to record your desktop efficiently
(VideoRecord plugin).

Captury supports full encoding as well as incremential(!) encoding by only
regions from the screen that have actually changed. Window managers
(like kwin) do know of such areas and can make use of it.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.7-1
  libcapseo0-0.3.0.20081031git-1bl1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libstdc++6-4.3.4-3
  libX11_6-1.3.3-1
  libXfixes3-4.0.5-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.65-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-10
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.10.0-1
  gawk-3.1.8-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  gcc4-g++-4.3.4-3
  libtool-2.2.11a-1
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.gitorious.net/libcaptury

Canonical download:
  libcaptury-0.3.0.20081031git.tar.bz2 

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libcaptury-0.3.0.20081031git-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libcaptury-0.3.0.20081031git-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libcaptury-0.3.0.20081031git-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libcaptury-0.3.0.20081031git-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libcaptury0-0.3.0.20081031git-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libcaptury-devel-0.3.0.20081031git-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

